  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the safety and effectiveness of cryoablation and
      radiofrequency ablation in the treatment of the commonest kind of supraventricular
      tachycardia, namely atrioventricular nodal reentrant tachycardia. The study hypothesis is
      that cryoablation is non-inferior to radiofrequency.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
